<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> ellensburg, washington 6/1/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.89)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9268'>Mike "the Mad Maia" French</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9268&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 1, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> i&#39;m mike french.  this is the second LOTR tourney in ellensburg ever, with my brother ryan as TD.  i&#39;ve been preparing for a long long time.  i hope to win, or at least place 2nd like i did last time.  i&#39;m playing gandalf mini-super fellowship (ie focus on gandalf and aragorn and frodo, plus gimli w/axe and arwen w/sword) and anti-super fellowship uruks with savagery up the wazoo (about 32-33 cards each side, i cant remember).  i start gimli and arwen, prancing pony for aragorn, and carry 4 gandalf&#39;s plus wiz is never late.  its basically the same as my posted &quot;Duel of the Wizards&quot; deck.  plus today i wore my duct-taped nike baseball cap.  i figure that one dude has that &quot;twinkie pants&quot; tech, i might as well have duct tape tech.  <br>
<br>
game one: i get matched against my brother, ryan french.  in 9 games out of 10 while we playtested, i won.  but he&#39;s playing good today.  he gets his desperate defenses and utwe&#39;s going, and tries to whittle down  my fellowship.  but i get a timely sleep caradhras and push on for the  site 9 win.  this was a close, close game, but i slowed him down enough for me to win.<br>
<br>
FW +3<br>
T 3<br>
<br>
highs: i won a close game.  i love winning close games.  my duct tape tech is working beautifully.<br>
<br>
lows: beating my poor brother.  he can never beat me.  sometimes i feel sorry for him.  then i laugh cause i always beat him.<br>
<br>
<br>
game two: i get matched up with a 12-year old kid, who eventually gets 8th place out of 9 and wins the &quot;participation&quot; award.  he&#39;s playing weak uruk-hai, with no savageries and few rares.  when he saw the amount of rares i owned (not too impressive, but i have a good number) he asked me if i was &quot;from Decipher&quot; like i was some angel sent from heaven or something.  so this game wasnt too much trouble.  the problem was he kept watching other people&#39;s games and getting distracted, so i made sure i killed him at site 6 before time ran out.<br>
<br>
FW +3 <br>
T 6<br>
<br>
highs: easy win, deck worked like a charm, even taught the kid some strategy along the way.  and my duct tape tech sticks around for another win.  get it?  sticks around?  hahaha<br>
<br>
lows: i never like beating little kids.  call me sentimental...or maybe its because my daddy beat me every day till i was 12 and i have psychological damage.  nah, i&#39;m just sentimental.<br>
<br>
<br>
game 3: next i get matched up to an 11 year-old named gabe who got last at our previous tourney.  before explaining this game, let me sidetrack for a moment.  about a half-hour before the tourney started, i asked anyone if they wanted to play a fun game.  gabe said sure.  so he goes first, i do fine until site 3.  he gets blade tips and black breaths out and puts them on gimli and arwen.  ouch.  gimli and arwen die.  then he gets nasty nazgul out and i cant find any servant of the secret fires.  bad.  gandalf dies.  i cant draw sam either.  i&#39;m down to aragorn and frodo, praying that i&#39;ll draw valiant man of the west.  i do draw one.  but he gets 3 minions out and kills me because of the fierce skirmishes.  by now, i&#39;m a little upset that i couldnt get rid of the black breaths and blade tips.  so before the tourney starts i add a second sleep caradhras.  so i&#39;m a little nervous when i&#39;m matched up to him in the tourney.  but i get the god draw for my fellowship, and double move every turn (even skipping site 6 sanctuary).  meanwhile my uruks are giving him trouble, and he only gets 2 or 3 of his black conditions out all game (and i slept them).  site 9 win in less than 25 minutes.<br>
<br>
FW +3<br>
T 9<br>
<br>
highs: i didnt lose horribly like i did in the warmup game.  and i like winning.  go duct tape!<br>
<br>
lows: i dont like beating little kids.  it makes me twitch.<br>
<br>
<br>
half hour break.  me, tom, and casey start a 3 player game just for the heck of it.  i have a dime for my marker, casey has a penny, and tom buys a bag of m&m&#39;s, eats them , and rips out the little yellow peanut M&M guy and uses him as his counter.  it was really funny.  we have to cut the game short, but i&#39;m obviously winning at site 4.  ok, maybe it wasnt that obvious, but who cares.<br>
<br>
<br>
game 4: me and greg anderson, from richland, are the only undefeated dudes left.  so after a little break, we go at it.  he bids 5, i bid 0.  he goes first, starting green dragon, depriving me of my prancing pony.  grr.  but i draw aragorn in my starting hand.  unfortunately i get little other help.  i stop him at site 2.  i move on to site 3, but i lose arwen due to a stupid lurtz&#39;s battle cry.  so i&#39;m feeling good, and he keeps saying, &quot;oh man i didnt want to let you get ahead.  oh man.&quot;  he moves to site 3 and stops.  i move to site 4 and get blasted by some uruks, and i&#39;m forced to stop.  he&#39;s at rivendell waterfall, he has like 6 companions, and i cant get a savagery in my hand if my life depended on it.  in a herioc feat, he triples moves, killing my uruks with archery and stuff.  i&#39;m upset.  i figure i&#39;m dead, so i dont try to catch up with my fellowship (like i could if i had tried).  i start discarding fp stuff and trying to draw into shadow.  that fails.  he moves to site 7.  stops. he moves to site 8. stops.  he moves to site nine (tol brandir), i get out 7 minions to his 5.  but he kills one with greenleaf, and exerts his woundless aragorn until he&#39;s defender +3.  i lose.  badly.<br>
<br>
FL +1<br>
T 10<br>
<br>
highs: i&#39;m more physically attractive than my opponent was.<br>
<br>
lows: losing that badly makes me really really mad.  it also makes me wanna go out and beat some little kids.  i&#39;m gonna throw away my duct tape hat.<br>
<br>
<br>
game 5: i figure if i win out, and greg loses one or two, i could still get first.  i&#39;m playing casey honeysett, who up to this point is 3-1 with a bye, his only loss to greg.  this game was weird.  casey was playing a weird uruk-hai nazgul mix, and it worked well for him.  he kills a few of my companions, and i think i&#39;m doing all right, until he kills everyone but aragorn and frodo.  aragorn is exhausted.  but i have valiant man of the west in my hand as i move to site nine.  he plays two uruks and some nazgul.  i figure i could win, since i have o elbereth to cancel a skirmish with the nazgul.  but then he plays saruman&#39;s frost.  so my frodo is power 3.  his lowest power uruk is 7.  no bounder.  PATHS is in my hand, but all of his minions have 2 or 3 vitality left.  at this point, i&#39;m a little upset.  if i had one more vitality on aragorn, i could win by putting both uruks on him, not being overwhelmed and taking one wound (cause of valiant man), canceling the skirmish with frodo and the nazgul with o elbereth.  then the nazgul could kill aragorn on the fierce skirmish and frodo would survive.  but aragorn is exhausted.  if i had sting, i could win cause frodo could skirmish a 7 strength uruk and survive, then skirmish the fierce nazgul and cancel it with elbereth.  if i had albert dreary out i could win by discarding the frosts.  but i dont, and i lose.<br>
<br>
FL +1<br>
T 11<br>
<br>
highs: i was totally bashing up his fellowship.  and i have more rares than casey, so nyah nyah nyah!<br>
<br>
lows:  i lost a close game. i really really hate losing close games.  losing close games makes me want to go out and beat little kids.<br>
<br>
<br>
game 6: final game.  since i&#39;ve already played everyone in the top 4, i&#39;m matched up to phil wheeler, who&#39;s 2-3 so far, with 2 close losses.  he&#39;s playing nazgul.  i think he went first and made it to site 2.  but on my first fellowship i get out gandalf and aragorn with weapons.  he&#39;s upset.  what makes him more upset is the fact that he has no minions.  he plays 2 black breaths and 2 blade tips.  i move.  he has one nazgul.  he plays 1 more of each black condition.  aragorn loses to his nazgul and gets a black eye.  he gets to the sanctuary.  i sleep caradhras his 6 black conditions, leaving phil in a somewhat irritated state, but he&#39;s still a good sport.  his nazgul dont even dent me.  i move and double move with pleasure.  i get to site 7 and stop.  he&#39;s at site 5 i think.  he gets to the sanctuary (barely).  i move to 8, and then to 9.  he&#39;s got nobody left after i killed his 2 nazgul at site 8.  i have aragorn with brand and sword, gandalf with staff and sword, arwen with sword, gimli, and frodo with sword and o elbereth.  i tell him he can have all the twilight he wants, cause its obvious that i&#39;m gonna win.  so he plays 5 nazgul. oops. including the witchking (non-twilight).  he plays a black steed, the pale blade, and morgul blade on the witch king, bumping him up to 28 power.  gandalf had his staff and no wounds.  i kill most of his remaining nazgul.  even with 5 fierce nazgul it wasnt really challenging (and i was holding a PATHS and valiant man of the west).  so i win.<br>
<br>
FW +3<br>
T 14<br>
<br>
highs:  we had fun.  i&#39;ve never seen a 28 power witch king, so that was nice.<br>
<br>
lows: none.<br>
<br>
<br>
the tourney ends with a clear winner, greg anderson going undefeated.  but there are 4 people with 14 points, including me, my brother ryan, casey honeysett, and gabe.  in the final round, ryan beat casey with a timely enduring evil against frodo to throw us all into a tie.  interestingly, i beat ryan, ryan beat casey, and casey beat me.  but Strength of Schedule decides ties.  as it turns out, ryan has a better SoS than me or casey, so he gets 2nd.  final rankings:<br>
<br>
1 greg anderson 18<br>
2 ryan french 14<br>
3 mike french 14<br>
4 casey honeysett 14<br>
5 gabe barker 14<br>
6 tom potter 12<br>
7 phil wheeler 10<br>
8 nate pennington 8<br>
9 ben freeman 7<br>
<br>
props and slops!<br>
<br>
props:<br>
<br>
mike the card shop owner.  just because he has a cool name.<br>
my brother ryan for running a fun and exciting tourney.<br>
greg anderson for driving the 1 1/2 hours and kicking all our butts.<br>
tom and casey for driving from leavenworth to put us over 8 so we were sanctioned.<br>
the little yellow peanut man for being the coolest marker.<br>
nate for losing every game but having fun.<br>
duct tape for helping me into 3rd.<br>
<br>
<br>
slops:<br>
<br>
mike the card shop owner for running out of boosters, even if it was the shipping company&#39;s fault.  =(<br>
duct tape for failing me when i needed it most.<br>
people who beat little kids.<br>
dennis jeffris, for not showing up due to SAT&#39;s.  come on, man, get your priorities straight!!<br>
ian hunter, for not coming.<br>
casey merry, for not coming.<br>
<br>
next tourney on my schedule is the territorial open in seattle on the 15th of june.  i plan on wearing my duct tape tech hat and winning.  if i dont win, i hope i can at least beat some little kids to satisfy my rage. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3705&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
